the music video was totally unexpected but also an amazing departure from their image as "idols who don't go near girls at all", the message was clear: they were able to have the time of their lives when they were away from the scrutinizing eyes of the public/media

the fashion!!! can we talk about the fact that kibum alone turned headbands and jerseys into a trend that summer in south korea? seeing a group of idols wearing such laidback clothes for their concept/stages was never done before, they are the blueprint for real

the choreography got praised for being easy to follow but so "shinee like" that no one else could do it. their vibe, technique and the amount of work they put into the simplest details is what makes it so legendary, view is probably my most watched song when it comes to fancams

having a deep house sound as your tt when everyone in the industry was doing the complete opposite remains an incredible gamble on their part, because yeah it's shinee and they always experiment but this song was still a big risk, yet here we are years later still praising it

in terms of music it was the first time jonghyun was truly put to the spotlight for his writing/composing skills, it was the start of his reputation as a lyrical and musical genius and an all around artist who put his everything into his craft
shinee's 'odd' era was and still is revolutionary to this day
